10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Figma AI is best suited for UI/UX designers, design teams, product teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Tome, meanwhile, shines for sales teams, founders, creative professionals, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Figma AI describes itself as \"Professional UI design tool with AI-powered design assistance features.\" Tome, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI-powered storytelling and presentation platform for modern teams.\" With 8 years between them, Figma AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Tome offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Figma AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Tome is a poor choice — far from it. Tome excels in its own right, particularly for sales teams and founders.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value industry-standard ui design tool, go with Figma AI. If ai generates entire narratives matters more to you, Tome is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
